This paper is primarily focused on natural language transduction problems, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also proposes new memory-based recurrent networks, which involves machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper uses synthetic grammars to simulate real-world transduction problems, which could potentially fall under computer vision (cs.CV) as well.
